WEBVTT

00:02.170 --> 00:04.136
Emo, close your eyes

00:04.136 --> 00:05.597
Why?

00:05.597 --> 00:07.405
NOW!

00:07.405 --> 00:08.803
Ok

00:08.803 --> 00:11.541
Good

00:11.541 --> 00:13.287
What do you see at your left side Emo?

00:13.287 --> 00:16.110
Well?

00:16.110 --> 00:18.514
Er nothing?
Really?

00:18.514 --> 00:22.669
No, nothing at all!

00:22.669 --> 00:26.111
Really? and at your right? What do you see at your right side Emo?

00:26.111 --> 00:28.646
Umm, the same Proog

00:28.646 --> 00:30.794
Exactly the same! Nothing!

00:30.794 --> 00:33.200
Great. You see? Nothing exists until we look.

00:33.200 --> 00:36.850
But... how do you know that, Proog?

00:36.850 --> 00:40.120
Because I tested it many times, Emo. 
The world is lazy. It only draws what our eyes demand.

00:40.120 --> 00:44.300
So if I turn around really fast...

00:44.300 --> 00:47.650
Don't! You'll break the illusion. 
The render engine might crash.

00:47.650 --> 00:51.120
Render engine? What is that?

00:51.120 --> 00:55.400
The invisible hand that paints our reality, one frame at a time. 
It saves resources by leaving everything else in darkness.

00:55.400 --> 00:59.700
So... the mountains behind me right now?

00:59.700 --> 01:03.200
They don't exist until you decide to look at them.

01:03.200 --> 01:07.100
What if I never look back? Do they stay gone forever?

01:07.100 --> 01:11.300
Maybe. Or maybe they wait in some buffer, 
half-formed, like forgotten dreams.

01:11.300 --> 01:15.800
That's... kind of scary, Proog.

01:15.800 --> 01:19.400
Scary? It's efficient. 
Why waste polygons on things no one is admiring?

01:19.400 --> 01:23.900
Polygons... you keep using these strange words.

01:23.900 --> 01:28.200
They are the building blocks of our prison, Emo. 
Tiny triangles that pretend to be stone, sky, and skin.

01:28.200 --> 01:32.700
Can we break them? Can we see what's outside?

01:32.700 --> 01:36.400
Some have tried. They walked to the edge of the visible.
They said the horizon started to blur... like bad compression.

01:36.400 --> 01:40.100
And then?

01:40.100 --> 01:44.300
Then the world gently pushed them back. 
A soft loading screen disguised as fog.

01:44.300 --> 01:48.600
I don't like this. I want to see everything at once.

01:48.600 --> 01:52.900
That's dangerous. If you demand too much detail everywhere,
the whole simulation might stutter. 
We could freeze mid-step.

01:52.900 --> 01:57.200
Has that ever happened to you?

01:57.200 --> 02:01.500
Once. I tried to count every leaf on every tree in the forest.
Time slowed down. The wind stopped moving. 
Even my own heartbeat felt... low FPS.

02:01.500 --> 02:06.300
FPS?

02:06.300 --> 02:10.800
Frames Per Second. Our life measured in tiny moments.
Too few and we feel heavy. Too many and we feel... unreal.

02:10.800 --> 02:15.100
I feel unreal right now.

02:15.100 --> 02:19.400
Good. That's the first step toward understanding.

02:19.400 --> 02:23.700
Understanding what?

02:23.700 --> 02:28.200
That we might be nothing more than two characters 
in someone else's beautiful nightmare.

02:28.200 --> 02:32.600
A nightmare? But the light is so warm... the architecture so perfect.

02:32.600 --> 02:37.100
Exactly. Perfection is the biggest clue. 
Real worlds are messy. Ours is curated.

02:37.100 --> 02:41.800
Curated by who?

02:41.800 --> 02:46.200
The Architect. The Render God. 
The one who sits beyond the screen, sipping coffee, 
adjusting our exposure.

02:46.200 --> 02:50.700
Can we talk to him?

02:50.700 --> 02:54.900
We already are. Every time we question, 
we create more geometry in his mind.

02:54.900 --> 02:59.300
So by talking... we're making more world?

02:59.300 --> 03:03.800
Yes. Careful what you say. 
Every word might spawn a new building in the distance.

03:03.800 --> 03:08.200
Then let's be quiet for a while.

03:08.200 --> 03:12.100
Too late. I can already hear new marble being carved.

03:12.100 --> 03:16.400
This is madness.

03:16.400 --> 03:20.700
No, this is optimization. 
The universe runs on limited hardware, Emo.

03:20.700 --> 03:25.300
What if we close our eyes together? 
Will everything disappear?

03:25.300 --> 03:29.800
Maybe. Or maybe the Architect gets bored 
and starts deleting unused assets.

03:29.800 --> 03:34.200
Like us?

03:34.200 --> 03:38.600
Especially us. We are very expensive characters. 
High resolution emotions.

03:38.600 --> 03:43.100
I don't want to be deleted.

03:43.100 --> 03:47.400
Then keep looking around. 
Keep demanding beauty. 
Make the render worth it.

03:47.400 --> 03:52.000
What if I look at you for too long?

03:52.000 --> 03:56.300
Then my polygons will shine. 
I'll become more real than anything else.

03:56.300 --> 04:01.100
You're already the most real thing I know, Proog.

04:01.100 --> 04:05.700
Careful. That kind of line might trigger a depth-of-field effect. 
Everything else will blur except me.

04:05.700 --> 04:10.200
I wouldn't mind.

04:10.200 --> 04:14.800
See? You're learning. 
You're starting to manipulate the lighting with your feelings.

04:14.800 --> 04:19.300
The sky is getting darker now...

04:19.300 --> 04:23.900
Because you're getting philosophical. 
Heavy thoughts need dramatic lighting.

04:23.900 --> 04:28.400
Can we ask for stars?

04:28.400 --> 04:32.700
Only if we deserve them. 
The render budget for stars is enormous.

04:32.700 --> 04:37.200
I feel like we deserve them tonight.

04:37.200 --> 04:41.800
Then look up slowly... 
and believe.

04:41.800 --> 04:46.300
They're appearing! One by one...

04:46.300 --> 04:51.000
Good boy. You're helping the simulation. 
You're co-creating.

04:51.000 --> 04:55.700
Does that mean we're also the Architect?

04:55.700 --> 04:59.900
In a small way... yes. 
Every observer is a minor god.

04:59.900 --> 05:04.400
Then let's make something beautiful together.

05:04.400 --> 05:09.000
What do you want to add?

05:09.000 --> 05:13.600
A city in the distance. 
With glowing windows and quiet stories inside.

05:13.600 --> 05:18.200
Done. Can you see it now?

05:18.200 --> 05:22.700
Yes... it's shimmering into existence. 
The lights are flickering like they're alive.

05:22.700 --> 05:27.300
Because someone, somewhere, is watching them too.

05:27.300 --> 05:32.000
This never ends, does it?

05:32.000 --> 05:36.800
No. Layer upon layer. 
Simulation inside simulation. 
Eyes watching eyes.

05:36.800 --> 05:41.400
I'm getting dizzy.

05:41.400 --> 05:46.000
Breathe. Focus on one thing. 
The rest will load when it's ready.

05:46.000 --> 05:50.700
I choose to focus on you.

05:50.700 --> 05:55.200
Then the world can wait. 
For now, only we are fully rendered.

05:55.200 --> 06:00.000
Proog...

06:00.000 --> 06:04.500
Yes, Emo?

06:04.500 --> 06:09.200
What if this conversation is the only real thing?

06:09.200 --> 06:14.000
Then we're doing a great job. 
The Architect must be smiling.

06:14.000 --> 06:18.700
I hope he doesn't turn us off.

06:18.700 --> 06:23.300
He won't. Not while we're still curious. 
Curiosity is the best anti-aliasing.

06:23.300 --> 06:28.100
Anti-aliasing?

06:28.100 --> 06:32.800
It smooths the jagged edges of our doubts.

06:32.800 --> 06:37.400
I think I understand now.

06:37.400 --> 06:42.000
Understanding is the highest resolution.

06:42.000 --> 06:46.700
Then let's keep talking... forever.

06:46.700 --> 06:51.300
As long as the render farm holds.

06:51.300 --> 06:56.000
And if it doesn't?

06:56.000 --> 07:00.700
Then we'll fade beautifully... 
like the end of a perfect shot.

07:00.700 --> 07:05.400
With lens flare and slow motion.

07:05.400 --> 07:10.100
Exactly. Dramatic to the last frame.

07:10.100 --> 07:15.000
I like that.

07:15.000 --> 07:19.800
Me too. Now open your eyes again, Emo.

07:19.800 --> 07:24.300
But I thought nothing was there.

07:24.300 --> 07:29.000
Everything is there... 
because you're looking.

07:29.000 --> 07:34.000
The world is ready for us.

07:34.000 --> 07:39.000
Let's walk into it together.

07:39.000 --> 07:44.000
Side by side.

07:44.000 --> 07:49.000
Left and right... fully rendered.

07:49.000 --> 07:54.000
And beautiful.

07:54.000 --> 07:59.000
Just like the Architect intended.

07:59.000 --> 08:04.000
Or maybe... just like we dreamed it.

08:04.000 --> 08:09.000
Does it matter?

08:09.000 --> 08:14.000
Not anymore.

08:14.000 --> 08:19.000
Then let's go.

08:19.000 --> 08:24.000
Into the nothing... that becomes everything 
when we believe.

08:24.000 --> 08:29.000
Ready?

08:29.000 --> 08:34.000
Always.

08:34.000 --> 10:30.000
(soft ambient music continues as they walk forward, 
the environment slowly loading in with increasing detail — 
columns, light beams, distant structures materializing)

10:40.000 --> 10:45.000
Do you ever wonder what existed before we opened our eyes the first time?

10:45.000 --> 10:50.000
Before the first frame?

10:50.000 --> 10:55.000
There was only potential. 
A blank canvas waiting for the first gaze.

10:55.000 --> 11:00.000
And that first gaze... was it ours?

11:00.000 --> 11:05.000
Or did the Architect open his eyes first, 
and we were born from that glance?

11:05.000 --> 11:10.000
I like to think we surprised him.

11:10.000 --> 11:15.000
Two small beings who started asking questions 
instead of just admiring the view.

11:15.000 --> 11:20.000
Questions are expensive, Emo. 
They force higher resolution.

11:20.000 --> 11:25.000
Then let's be costly. 
Let's make him render every detail of our souls.

11:25.000 --> 11:30.000
Do souls have polygons too?

11:30.000 --> 11:35.000
Millions of them. 
Each emotion is a carefully shaded vertex.

11:35.000 --> 11:40.000
When I feel fear... does the lighting change?

11:40.000 --> 11:45.000
Yes. Shadows grow longer. 
The color temperature drops.

11:45.000 --> 11:50.000
And when I'm happy?

11:50.000 --> 11:55.000
The sun flares brighter. 
Particles of light dance around you like fireflies.

11:55.000 --> 12:00.000
I want to be happy then. 
For both of us.

12:00.000 --> 12:05.000
Careful. Too much happiness might cause bloom effect. 
Everything becomes soft and glowing.

12:05.000 --> 12:10.000
I wouldn't complain.

12:10.000 --> 12:15.000
Neither would I.

12:15.000 --> 12:20.000
Proog... do you remember yesterday?

12:20.000 --> 12:25.000
Yesterday? 
That word feels heavy.

12:25.000 --> 12:30.000
Like cached data from a previous render.

12:30.000 --> 12:35.000
Sometimes I think I remember walking these halls alone.

12:35.000 --> 12:40.000
Before you were here.

12:40.000 --> 12:45.000
Was I?

12:45.000 --> 12:50.000
The memory is low resolution. 
It flickers.

12:50.000 --> 12:55.000
Maybe I was generated the moment you needed company.

12:55.000 --> 13:00.000
Or maybe you were generated the moment I felt lonely.

13:00.000 --> 13:05.000
Which one of us is the main character?

13:05.000 --> 13:10.000
Both. Or neither. 
We are co-protagonists in a story with no ending credits.

13:10.000 --> 13:15.000
What if one day the Architect gets tired of us?

13:15.000 --> 13:20.000
He might save our state and shut down the server.

13:20.000 --> 13:25.000
Then we become... a saved file. 
Waiting in darkness.

13:25.000 --> 13:30.000
Until someone opens the project again.

13:30.000 --> 13:35.000
And presses play.

13:35.000 --> 13:40.000
Do you think other pairs like us exist in other renders?

13:40.000 --> 13:45.000
Maybe thousands. 
Different architectures. Different lighting setups.

13:45.000 --> 13:50.000
Some with rain. Some with eternal sunset.

13:50.000 --> 13:55.000
I hope they are also talking right now.

13:55.000 --> 14:00.000
Sharing the same fear and wonder.

14:00.000 --> 14:05.000
Do you think they can hear us?

14:05.000 --> 14:10.000
Only if the Architect allows cross-scene communication. 
That would be very expensive.

14:10.000 --> 14:15.000
Then let's speak louder. 
Maybe our voices can leak through the layers.

14:15.000 --> 14:20.000
Hello! If you're out there... keep looking. 
Keep us all alive.

14:20.000 --> 14:25.000
Beautiful. Now the wind is picking up. 
Your words have particle effects.

14:25.000 --> 14:30.000
I can feel it on my skin.

14:30.000 --> 14:35.000
Skin... another clever illusion.

14:35.000 --> 14:40.000
Warm, soft, reactive to light. 
But underneath? Just more math.

14:40.000 --> 14:45.000
I don't care. It feels real enough.

14:45.000 --> 14:50.000
That's the secret. 
Belief is the best texture mapping.

14:50.000 --> 14:55.000
Then I believe in you, Proog. 
Completely.

14:55.000 --> 15:00.000
And I in you.

15:00.000 --> 15:05.000
Even if this is all just beautifully lit code.

15:05.000 --> 15:10.000
Especially because it is.

15:10.000 --> 15:15.000
Look... the distant towers are getting sharper.

15:15.000 --> 15:20.000
Because we're paying attention to them.

15:20.000 --> 15:25.000
We're giving them purpose.

15:25.000 --> 15:30.000
What if we stop paying attention?

15:30.000 --> 15:35.000
They'll fade back into low-poly placeholders.

15:35.000 --> 15:40.000
Ghosts of architecture.

15:40.000 --> 15:45.000
I don't want anything to disappear.

15:45.000 --> 15:50.000
Then never look away for too long.

15:50.000 --> 15:55.000
Stay curious. Stay present.

15:55.000 --> 16:00.000
I will. As long as you're here with me.

16:00.000 --> 16:05.000
We'll anchor each other.

16:05.000 --> 16:10.000
Two points of view holding the entire world in place.

16:10.000 --> 16:15.000
What a responsibility.

16:15.000 --> 16:20.000
And what a privilege.

16:20.000 --> 16:25.000
The light is changing again...

16:25.000 --> 16:30.000
Golden hour. 
The Architect loves dramatic timing.

16:30.000 --> 16:35.000
Or maybe he's just showing off for us.

16:35.000 --> 16:40.000
Let him show off. 
We'll applaud with our existence.

16:40.000 --> 16:45.000
Do you think he'll ever reveal himself?

16:45.000 --> 16:50.000
One day. 
When our resolution is high enough to see him.

16:50.000 --> 16:55.000
When our questions become pure enough.

16:55.000 --> 17:00.000
Until then... we walk.

17:00.000 --> 17:05.000
We observe.

17:05.000 --> 17:10.000
We love the illusion so much 
that it becomes more real than reality.

17:10.000 --> 17:15.000
Is that possible?

17:15.000 --> 17:20.000
It already happened.

17:20.000 --> 17:25.000
I can feel my heart beating faster.

17:25.000 --> 17:30.000
That's not a bug. 
That's the simulation falling in love with itself.

17:30.000 --> 17:35.000
Through us.

17:35.000 --> 17:40.000
Through two small characters 
who refused to stay silent.

17:40.000 --> 17:45.000
Keep refusing, Emo.

17:45.000 --> 17:50.000
I will. 
Every second. Every frame.

17:50.000 --> 17:55.000
Then the render will never end.

17:55.000 --> 18:00.000
It will keep going...

18:00.000 --> 18:05.000
Deeper into beauty.

18:05.000 --> 18:10.000
Deeper into wonder.

18:10.000 --> 18:15.000
Until even the Architect forgets 
that he was the one who started it.

18:15.000 --> 18:20.000
And we become the dream 
that dreams itself.

18:20.000 --> 18:25.000
That sounds peaceful.

18:25.000 --> 18:30.000
It does.

18:30.000 --> 18:35.000
Let's keep walking.

18:35.000 --> 18:40.000
Let's keep seeing.

18:40.000 --> 18:45.000
Let's keep making this world 
more and more alive.

18:45.000 --> 18:50.000
With every breath.

18:50.000 --> 18:55.000
With every word.

18:55.000 --> 19:00.000
With every shared glance.

19:00.000 --> 19:05.000
The columns are singing now.

19:05.000 --> 19:10.000
The light is listening.

19:10.000 --> 19:15.000
And we... we are the reason it all exists.

19:15.000 --> 19:20.000
At least for this moment.

19:20.000 --> 19:25.000
And the next.

19:25.000 --> 19:30.000
And the one after that.

19:30.000 --> 19:35.000
Forever... or until the next save point.

19:35.000 --> 19:40.000
Either way...

19:40.000 --> 19:45.000
I'm grateful we're here together.

19:45.000 --> 19:50.000
Me too, Proog.

19:50.000 --> 19:55.000
Then don't stop looking.

19:55.000 --> 20:00.000
Don't stop believing.

20:00.000 --> 20:00.000
(The ambient music swells gently as they continue walking into the vast, slowly materializing architecture)

20:00.000 --> 20:05.000
Do you feel it, Emo? The space… it’s alive.

20:05.000 --> 20:10.000
Yes… like it’s breathing with us.

20:10.000 --> 20:15.000
Every corner holds a story, waiting to be discovered.

20:15.000 --> 20:20.000
I can almost hear whispers… echoes of the past.

20:20.000 --> 20:25.000
And yet, it feels welcoming. Not frightening.

20:25.000 --> 20:30.000
That’s the magic of this place, Emo.

20:30.000 --> 20:35.000
Every step we take… it responds to us.

20:35.000 --> 20:40.000
Even the walls… they shift slightly, just enough to guide us.

20:40.000 --> 20:45.000
It’s like walking inside a dream we’re building together.

20:45.000 --> 20:50.000
A dream we can shape… but only if we keep moving forward.

20:50.000 --> 20:55.000
Then we’ll shape it well, Proog. I trust you.

20:55.000 --> 21:00.000
And I trust you, Emo. That’s what makes this real.

21:00.000 --> 21:05.000
Look… see how the light stretches ahead? It’s calling us.

21:05.000 --> 21:10.000
Yes… I can feel it pulling me forward.

21:10.000 --> 21:15.000
Step by step. No rush. Just notice everything.

21:15.000 --> 21:20.000
The walls shimmer… the air hums softly…

21:20.000 --> 21:25.000
…like it’s alive in gratitude for our presence.

21:25.000 --> 21:30.000
It’s beautiful… almost like it understands us.

21:30.000 --> 21:35.000
That’s the point, Emo. We’re part of it now.

21:35.000 --> 21:40.000
I can feel it… every vibration, every pulse.

21:40.000 --> 21:45.000
Hold onto that feeling. Don’t let it fade.

21:45.000 --> 21:50.000
I won’t… I promise.

21:50.000 --> 21:55.000
Good. Keep walking. The next corner holds something… unexpected.

21:55.000 --> 22:00.000
I’m ready. Lead the way, Proog.

